Ų[{"URL":"/image/332be17c3f096b4c4edbaace00304527f7a3b7b2","importURL":"https://www.geograph.org.uk/photo/4776496","licence":"CC BY-SA 2.0","media_type":"bench","sha1":"332be17c3f096b4c4edbaace00304527f7a3b7b2","width":4896,"height":3672},{"URL":"/image/ca5cdf368a24090171c08c9c8cf16ad0f9b481db","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"inscription","sha1":"ca5cdf368a24090171c08c9c8cf16ad0f9b481db","width":4032,"height":3024},{"URL":"/image/db54e29e477bb7e181970b26a5694bad65843028","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"pano","sha1":"db54e29e477bb7e181970b26a5694bad65843028","width":4096,"height":1379},{"URL":"/image/25147126f701d5419fdac4c4d7e3319636d14c94","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"bench","sha1":"25147126f701d5419fdac4c4d7e3319636d14c94","width":4032,"height":3024},{"URL":"/image/b1cc17f381fee64352b3e33c0a2aecb606565375","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"view","sha1":"b1cc17f381fee64352b3e33c0a2aecb606565375","width":4032,"height":3024}]"╬
╦This Bench and the Golden Roses planted either side of
the Gardener's Hut are to commemorate the work of
JOHN SPEED
the Gardener in Golden Square and
Leicester Square Gardens who died in October 2002"Ž
╠IN TREASURED MEMORY OF MY DARLING HUSBAND
FRANIE DANIELS 25.10.1910 - 15.2.1992
HIS BUSINESS WAS IN MOUNT STREET
TOGETHER WE SHARED THIS SECRET GARDEN
FOR EVER AND ALWAYS AND ALL ETERNITY YOUR SHELAGH"Ž
╠In Loving Memory
RONALD HALL                                             LOUISA HALL
25/11/1927           TRUE EASTENDERS       21/11/1930
  TO                                                                         TO
15/10/2003                                                       29/12/2007

Back Together Again
Their life together started the day they met by this lake,
So it seems only right to celebrate their lives by
placing this plaque here
DAD & MUM
If tears could build a stairway and memories a lane
I'd walk right up to heaven and bring ya home again
Luv Ya 124"č
╬[LEFT]
SAM ROCHE
LOVING DAUGHTER, SISTER, MOTHER
TO THE WORLD YOU MAY HAVE BEEN SOMEBODY
BUT TO US YOU WERE THE WORLD

[RIGHT]
EMILY LEWIS
WONDERFUL MOTHER & GRANDMOTHER
ALWAYS LOVING: ALWAYS LOVED"▌
